      <div id='blog-post--capture-the-flag-20'>
<article class=''>

  <header>
    <a class="picture" href="../../country?country=CH&amp;redirect=%252Fabout#gdb">
      <img src="../../img/about/team/gdb@2x.jpeg">
    </a>
    <h1><a href="../../country?country=CH&amp;redirect=%252Fblog%252Fcapture-the-flag-20">Capture the Flag 2.0<br /></a></h1>
    <p>
      <a class="author" href="../../country?country=CH&amp;redirect=%252Fabout#gdb">Greg Brockman</a>
      <span>on</span> August 22, 2012
    </p>
  </header>
  
  <div class="content">
    <div class="image-center">
<img src="../../img/blog/posts/ctf-20/ctf20.png" class="no-border ctf-20" width="578" height="250" data-hires="true" />
</div>

<p> Today we're launching Capture the
Flag: Web Edition, a security contest where you can try your hand
at discovering and exploiting vulnerabilities in mock web
applications. If you've ever wondered how a <a
href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cross-site_request_forgery">CSRF
attack</a> works in practice, this is your chance to find out. We've
found that hands-on experience with exploiting security flaws helps us
write more secure code, and we hope that working on the CTF will be
both enlightening and fun. </p>

<p> To get started, simply create an account.
You'll be set up
with a series of levels; your goal for each level is to extract a
password to unlock the next one. If you successfully complete all
levels, we'll send you a special-edition Stripe Web CTF T-shirt,
designed just for this contest. You can keep tabs on how you're
doing relative to others on the
Capture the Flag
leaderboard. </p>

<hr>

<p> If you're not sure where to start,
the <a href="https://www.owasp.org/">Open Web Application Security
Project</a>
and <a href="http://code.google.com/p/browsersec/wiki/Main">Google
Browser Security Handbook</a> are great resources. You can also chat
with fellow solvers in
the CTF chatroom (also accessible in your favorite IRC client at
<a href="irc://irc.stripe.com:+6697/ctf">irc://irc.stripe.com:+6697/ctf</a>).
</p>

<p> If you have any questions, feel free to get in touch at
<a href="mailto:ctf@stripe.com">ctf@stripe.com</a>. Enjoy the challenge! </p>

<div class="map">
    <div class="map-details">
      <dl>
        <dt>Where:</dt>
        <dd>stripe-ctf.com</dd>
        <dt>Start:</dt>
        <dd>Wednesday, August 22nd, 2012<br/> at 12 noon PDT</dd>
        <dt>End:</dt>
        <dd>Wednesday, August 29th, 2012<br/> at 12 noon PDT</dd>
      </dl>
    </div>
</div>



  </div>

  <footer>
    <p>
      August 22, 2012
    </p>
